# Build context for `docker build` and `az acr build`. Keep it small and never
# bake secrets into the image.
#
# NOTE on patterns: az acr build's source packer honors .dockerignore but matches
# more literally than Docker/BuildKit. A trailing-slash directory pattern (e.g.
# `infra/`) is NOT honored, and a bare name only matches at the top level. So:
#   • top-level dir  → bare, no trailing slash        e.g. `infra`, `database`
#   • nested dir     → full path (or `**/` prefix)    e.g. `frontend/node_modules`
# Verify with `az acr build --debug`: it logs which rule matched each path
# (`rule '…' matches '…'` vs `no rule for '…'`).

# Git / editors / local tool state
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes
.vscode
.idea
.claude

# Secrets & environment — must never enter the image
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Node — dependencies are reinstalled inside the frontend build stage
node_modules
**/node_modules
frontend/node_modules
frontend/.vite

# Infra — Terraform state plus ~2 GB of downloaded provider binaries under
# .terraform; never needed to build or run the image. (Bare path: `infra/` is
# NOT honored by az acr build's packer — that was shipping the whole tree.)
infra

# Locally-built SPA — the image rebuilds it from source
backend/app/frontend

# Sample database scripts — not needed to build or run the image
database

# Python caches / virtualenvs
backend/.venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.py[cod]
**/.venv
**/venv
**/*.egg-info
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache

# Docs, licence, and local logs — not part of the runtime image
*.md
*.log
LICENSE

# OS cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
